Package: nclawzero-cerberus-helper
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Jason Perlow <jperlow@nvidia.com>
Installed-Size: 15
Depends: curl, python3
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Description: CERBERUS inference helper (idempotent curl wrapper)
 Thin wrapper around a local OpenAI-compatible inference endpoint
 (e.g. vLLM / llama.cpp server). Config-driven, no credentials, safe
 to re-run. Demonstrates the local consultative tier alongside the
 default cloud-consultative path.
 .
 Edit /etc/nclawzero/cerberus.conf to point at a different endpoint.
 Defaults to the author's lab inference server (CERBERUS, RTX 4500).
